  "content": "ID: T1547.010\nTitle: Boot or Logon Autostart Execution:Port Monitors\nURL: https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1547/010\nAdversaries may use port monitors to run an adversary supplied DLL during system boot for persistence or privilege escalation. A port monitor can be set through the AddMonitor API call to set a DLL to be loaded at startup. [1] This DLL can be located in C:\\Windows\\System32 and will be loaded and run by the print spooler service, spoolsv.exe , under SYSTEM level permissions on boot. [2] Alternatively, an arbitrary DLL can be loaded if permissions allow writing a fully-qualified pathname for that DLL to the Driver value of an existing or new arbitrarily named subkey of HKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Print\\Monitors . The Registry key contains entries for the following: Local Port Standard TCP/IP Port USB Monitor WSD Port",
  "category": "Article",
  "source": "Local Storage",
